&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the entire onboarding process for new hires, ensuring all procedures are followed promptly and efficiently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Hiring Managers to customize onboarding plans based on departmental needs and roles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop, implement, and update onboarding materials, including training presentations and handbooks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate orientation sessions for new employees, ensuring they receive a warm welcome and comprehensive introduction to the company culture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a first point of contact for new hires, addressing their questions and concerns throughout the onboarding process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Measure the effectiveness of onboarding programs through surveys and feedback and suggest improvements based on the results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with IT and facilities management to ensure that new hires have the necessary equipment and workspace prepared before their start date.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain the employee data, profile completion on the HRMS. Handling data changes from other functions and employees.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support payroll activities with incentives, allowance collations and coordination with departments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handling all the offboarding formalities and coordinating with HRBP, sub-functions and employees.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handling employee queries and closing the tickets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong experience in HRMS especially with onboarding, employee profile management, leaves and other employee life cycle processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Human Resources, Business Administration, or related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 6 to 9 years of experience in end-to-end HR Operations. Should have knowledge on payroll.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of HR best practices, employment laws, and regulatory requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to engage with individuals at all levels.&lt;/li&gt;
